mindmap
  root((AI Diffusion Strategy))
    Rogers Framework
      Adoption Curve
        Innovators - risk tolerant experimenters
        Early Adopters - visionary advantage seekers
        Majority - pragmatic proof seekers
      Five Perception Filters
        Relative advantage
        Compatibility
        Complexity and trialability
        Observability
    Barriers to Adoption
      Technical
        Data quality and access
        Integration friction
        Infrastructure constraints
      Organizational
        Fear of change and job loss
        Inertia and status quo pull
        Unclear incentives
      Cultural
        Black box distrust
        Loss of agency concerns
        Values misalignment
    Accelerators
      Executive Sponsorship
        Visible C-suite championing
        Resource allocation signals
      Incentive Alignment
        Metrics rewarding experimentation
        Recognition and career paths
      Social Proof
        Early wins shared internally
        Demo days and case studies
    Strategic Timing
      Wave-Based Rollout
        Start with curious motivated teams
        Prepare next wave during pilots
        Recognize when not to push
      Internal Variation
        Different teams at different stages
        Influence networks over org charts
        Peer proof drives adoption
    Leadership Mindset
      Empathy
        Fears are signals not resistance
        Inclusion in design process
      Structure
        Governance and ownership clarity
        Success measurement frameworks
      Momentum
        Amplify small wins
        Build internal AI brand